    A thread-safe storage for key -> value associations. Unlike ConcurrentHashMap, this map synchronizes writes since the multi-value associations require two independent read/writes to the map state; one to retrieve an existing collection, a second one to add another value to it.
    Note that it is not save to modify the contents of the collection returned by this map since it is still based on the contents of this map and not a shallow copy for performance considerations.
    In addition, the values stored in this map are distinct, i.e. if a value already exists in the values collection it is removed prior to the insertion of the new element.
